Comment: Why does this trailer use Under Pressure? It's a great song, but it has absolutely nothing to do with the trailer. The lyrics don't have any relevance, and it doesn't match the themes either. There is literally no reason for a great song to be in such a dumb trailer except to make people relate the song with the movie and think that the movie is as good as the song. (spoiler alert: It's not)

Title: Minions Official Trailer #1 (2015) - Despicable Me Prequel HD
Comment: I really don't like this movie. I admit I never actually bothered to see it, but my younger sisters who both love Despicable Me did, and they both walked out of the theatre disappointed by the lack of, well, anything. This movie is just filler created by Illumination because they know that people will see anything with Minions in it, whether it's an actual movie or just a 90 minute Despicable Me after credits scene that you have to pay to watch. They made $1 billion just by animating minions doing things, and they're going to do it again next year with Minions 2, a movie title I hoped I would never have to say. This movie only exists to take advantage of people who like Minions. I've heard from everyone I know whose seen this movie that there is really nothing of any value in it. The plot only exists because the movie needs to have a plot, there is no depth or good storytelling found anywhere, and the movie is just barely funny enough to keep you from getting bored, while never making you laugh or really feel amused. The fact that this is the second highest grossing animated movie of all time is just sickening. Please just take your kids to see Disney or Pixar movies instead, as they seem to be the only companies that care about making good movies more than they care about exploiting your sense of humour for money.
